Common name: Chinese tallow, Chicken tree, Candleberry tree.
Botanical name: Triadica sebifera
Places found: native to China, Taiwan, and Japan. It is also found in the India , US and France.
Medicinal uses:
1. The waxy coating of the seeds is used for candle and soap making, and the leaves are used as herbal medicine to treat boils.
2. It is useful in the production of biodiesel because it is the third most productive vegetable oil.
3. It has become a major honey plant for beekeepers.
